
'Basics:
Syntax for records, variants, and their types.

'Record types

:p {&}
> {&}

:p {a:Int & b:Float}
> {a: Int32 & b: Float32}

:p {a:Int & b:Float &}
> {a: Int32 & b: Float32}

:p {a:Int & a:Float}
> {a: Int32 & a: Float32}


'Records

:p {}
> {}
:t {}
> {&}

:p {,}
> {}
:t {,}
> {&}

:p {a=3, b=4}
> {a = 3, b = 4}
:t {a=3, b=4}
> {a: Nat & b: Nat}

:p {a=3, b=4,}
> {a = 3, b = 4}
:t {a=3, b=4,}
> {a: Nat & b: Nat}

:p {a=3, a=4}
> {a = 3, a = 4}
:t {a=3, a=4}
> {a: Nat & a: Nat}

:p
  x = {a=5.0, b=2}
  y : {a:Int & b:Int & ..._} = {a=3, a=4, ...x}
  y
> {a = 3, a = 4, a = 5., b = 2}

:p
  {b=b1, a=a1, c=c1, a=a2} = {a=1, a=2, b=3, c=4}
  (a1, a2, b1, c1)
> (1, (2, (3, 4)))

